I decided to start BJJ to improve my fitness levels and learn how to defend myself. I did feel a bit nervous walking into a new club and starting a sport I knew nothing about but I was immediately put at ease by everyone at Black Dog.

Everyone was really friendly and welcoming, and that makes all the difference to create an supportive atmosphere whilst you're learning new skills. Both Alex and Oly are really knowledgeable and break down the techniques in a way that makes it relatable to people instead of baffling them with jargon, and teach the fundamentals in a way that means they can be adapted to different situations, which I find really useful.

Members of the club are very encouraging and genuinely want to see each other improve as much as they want to improve themselves. When rolling or doing drills, everyone communicates well and are very considerate of each other when sparring with different skill levels, genders and age ranges which I personally feel makes me feel respected and safe when rolling.

Would definitely recommend Black Dog BJJ to anyone wanting learn self defense, improve their fitness and confidence, whilst making a few friends along the way!

text.text:
As a woman, when I first came here about 9 months ago, I was nervous entering into the self defence/MMA world. But the coaches were all so understanding and supportive. I have so many different training partners and they each teach me something new every time. As a severe introvert, over this time I learned new physical skills as well as social skills. In this time I’ve grown as an individual in so many ways and I’ve also done 2 interclubs, coming to my third next week. My intentions when I came here weren’t oriented toward competing or anything of the sort but I find that’s where I’m headed because of the quality of the training I receive here.

Coach Darren and Coach Rick are the main coaches and are truly brilliant. Salford MMA isn’t just a gym, it’s a community, I might even go so far as to say it’s a family, and I would recommend it to anyone who wants to explore their curiosity in the field.

They offer BJJ, no-gi grappling, wrestling, kickboxing, Muay Thai and more, but these are my personal favourites. Also, they have loads of bags, a cage, a ring, large matted areas, a big gym equipped area, a decent changing room for women and just awesome people. I love this place :)

Sale Ju-Jitsu Academy has provided my twin sons with an exceptional experience. From the moment we walked through the doors, the instructors greeted us with warmth and enthusiasm, creating a welcoming environment for both children and parents.
The instructors at Sale Ju-Jitsu Academy are highly skilled and dedicated to teaching the art of Ju-Jitsu. They possess a deep understanding of the discipline and are excellent at imparting their knowledge to the students. Their patience and encouragement have helped my sons progress in their skills and build their self-confidence.
The academy itself is well-maintained and equipped with the necessary facilities for effective training. The training sessions are structured, engaging, and cater to the needs of students at different skill levels. The instructors ensure that each child receives individual attention and guidance, fostering a sense of achievement and growth.
The academy promotes a positive and supportive atmosphere, fostering friendships and a sense of camaraderie among the students.
As a parent, I appreciate the clear communication and organization of the academy. The staff is approachable and always ready to address any concerns or queries we may have.
Attending Sale Ju-Jitsu Academy has not only improved my sons' physical fitness but has also instilled in them a sense of self-discipline, perseverance, and respect for others. Seeing their growth and enthusiasm after each session brings me great joy and reassurance that we made the right choice in enrolling them at this academy.
In conclusion, Sale Ju-Jitsu Academy offers an exceptional learning experience for children. With skilled instructors, a nurturing environment, and a focus on character development, it is an ideal place for children to learn Ju-Jitsu while gaining valuable life skills. My twin sons look forward to their Wednesday sessions with excitement and I am grateful for the positive impact the academy has had on their overall development.

My 7 year old son joined this gym just before it opened at start of year which unfortunately coincided with the lockdown in January 2021 and this meant he couldn't train in the academy in person when it first opened.

Depsite this Professor Mike and Coach T did an excellent job in difficult circumstances with their offering over Zoom which gave my son the foundations before he could get to the academy in April when restrictions eased. I was already impressed with what I had seen virtually over zoom however since he has started with classes in person I'm even more impressed.

Amazing set up, great atmosphere and brilliant place to not only learn Brazilian jiu-jitsu but also great life skills too. My son loves his classes that are mixture of fun games and technique that are really well structured.

The team at Gracie Barra Roundhay are super friendly and do a great job.

text.text:
I’ve been training at Gracie Barra Roundhay for just over two years now and there isn’t a part of my life that isn’t better off for it. The team have carefully created a wonderful environment for learning and self-development. From the excellent facilities (which include a coffee area complete with a mini library) to the skilled coaching team it comes together to make learning Brazilian Jiu Jitsu not only safe but fun. The timetable and classes are varied with sessions in the morning, lunch and evening which means you can train around your schedule. The structure of the classes and quality of the coaching make each session fun and engaging and the time flies by. So If you want to extend your session then you can make use of the well-stocked gym or recover in the sauna or ice bath.

It’s difficult to distil the impact it has had on me in a few short sentences but I’ll do my best. Some of things you might expect from learning Jiu Jitsu, my strength and mobility has significantly improved and my overall physical health is better. But other benefits have come from unexpected places. As a safe space to grow, the academy have cultivated an incredible and truly unique community and I am insanely proud to be part of it. I have found friendship and support from a team that inspire me to be better in every way. Even the way the academy commit to continual improvement and giving back to the community has inspired me to apply this to my own profession.

I urge anyone who might on the fence to give it a try. Every single one of us knows what is like to walk through those doors for the first time so you can expect a warm welcome when you do.

Amazing Jiu Jitsu club set up by Chau (The Owner). I’m a complete novice to Jiu Jitsu but have been in other combat sport gyms. The atmosphere inside Stealth BJJ Bolton is amazing. You feel at ease and welcomed. Everyone who I’ve encountered is so friendly and wants to help. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

The biggest worry for any white belt (like me) is going to a new gym and just getting smashed by other members. This doesn’t happen, the coaches make sure of that.

Chau is so attentive to everyone and looks after all skills levels. He will look after you and help you find your feet. He responds to calls and WhatsApps rapid.

Can’t wait to learn more of this fascinating Martial Art.

Keep it up Chau and team! 🥋
